line_1: And to my pen the task assign;
The gods to each a separate path assign,
line_2: Too high request in every sphere to shine,
'To triumph, and to die, are mine.'
'To triumph, and to die, are mine. '

line_1: How pleasing's the condition you assign?
line_2: Most noble 'Squire, more generous than your wine,

line_1: There should my hand no stinted boon assign
line_2: To wretched hearts with sorrows such as mine; —

line_1: It damps the Theists too, while they assign,
line_2: To Nature, what's done by a Power divine.

line_1: Argues it need no Deputies assign;
line_2: The Omnipresence, of the Power Divine,

line_1: Shall heaven to me the drear abode assign!
line_2: Of these, that rest beneath me, shall be mine.

line_1: Ere yet to buried ROSCIUS we assign —
line_2: One kind Regret — one tributary Line!
